703611f-a.title: Brooklyn: Classon Avenue - Willoughby Avenue
703611f-a.text:
Classon Ave., west side, at and north of Willoughby Ave. A view
of St. Mary's Episcopal Church and Rectory facing Classon Ave. The
Church was organised in 1835, the cornerstone laidin July 1858;
and it was opened for services in 1859.
1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
Same, showing more of the church.
1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
Same, showing the north side of the church.
1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(4)
Same, showing a further view of Classon Ave. Also seen is the
Myrtle Ave. Elevated line of the B.M.T. in the background.
1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
